Name: Naveen
AboutMe:
I started as Notes/Domino developer and worked on Notes client and web based applications. I also have a pretty good exposure to XPages. As Notes/Domino developer I was an active contributor to IBM’s open source initiative – OpenNTF. Some of my projects include Java Charts, Download all attachments and Timeago for XPages. You can view complete list of my contributions to OpenNTF over here. I also wrote couple of articles for Pipalia software house.

After working for 5 years in Notes/Domino, I switched to SharePoint and currently I am working on custom development in SharePoint with ASP.NET and C#. I would not consider myself a newbie in SharePoint but there’s a long road ahead before I become an expert :)

Apart from SharePoint and Notes, the latest developments in HTML5 and CSS3 interest me and I try to incorporate it in my projects.

You can connect with me on Twitter and LinkedIn.
